Package com.google.mu.protobuf.util

Interface ValueConverter

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,​com.google.protobuf.Value>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ValueConverter
extends java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,​com.google.protobuf.Value>
    A converter that can convert a Pojo to Value message, and recursively, the Collections, Maps and Tables thereof into corresponding ListValue or Struct wrappers.

    Users can implement custom conversion logic while delegating to MoreStructs for the standard supported types.

    Since:
    5.8

      • toStruct

        Returns a Collector that accumulates elements into a Struct whose keys and values are the result of applying the provided mapping functions to the input elements.

        Duplicate keys (according to Object.equals(Object)) are not allowed.

        Null keys are not allowed.

      • toStruct

        default BiCollector<java.lang.CharSequence,​java.lang.Object,​com.google.protobuf.Struct> toStruct()
        Returns a BiCollector that accumulates the name-value pairs into a Struct with the values converted using #toValue.

        Duplicate keys (according to Object.equals(Object)) are not allowed.

        Null keys are not allowed, but null values will be represented with NullValue.

        Can also be used to create Struct literals conveniently, such as: 

        
 BiStream.of("foo", 1. "bar", true).collect(converter.toStruct());
